22:25.520 --> 22:28.780
And Flyxion maps this out using persistent homology, doesn't he?

22:29.060 --> 22:29.480
He does.

22:29.700 --> 22:37.140
He tracks how the topological features of the memory space evolve or devolve during these infinite cost erasure events.

22:37.260 --> 22:38.780
The persistence module of memory.

22:38.960 --> 22:39.360
Exactly.

22:39.360 --> 22:46.320
He utilizes persistent homology to analyze the Betty numbers of the manifold as operators are iteratively removed.

22:46.320 --> 22:50.380
And he identifies highly distinct topological modes of collapse.

22:50.980 --> 22:54.880
The most immediate is zero-dimensional collapse or fragmentation.

